The paper discusses brain-inspired neuromorphic processors and their architectures that support models of cortical networks and deep neural networks. This falls under the category of neural networks and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.NE. The paper also discusses mixed analog/digital systems, which are related to electronic devices and circuits, covered by cs.ET. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of building artificial neural processing systems, which is related to robotics and control systems, covered by cs.AR and cs.SY. Finally, the paper discusses adaptation and learning mechanisms, which is related to machine learning, covered by cs.AI.
